# Constitution

Full detail: `.playbook/00_PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` (read before non-trivial change).

## Non-negotiable

1. Never delete information — archive it (`.playbook/12_DECISIONS.md`).
2. Preserve backwards compatibility; no silent rewrites of working content.
3. Never hardcode company/content in HTML — use `data/*.json`.
4. Content separate from rendering.
5. Vanilla JS + hand-written CSS (`assets/css/site.css`) only — no frameworks/CSS CDN. No request-time build; exception: `npm run prerender` bakes `data/*.json` into committed `index.html`/`sitemap.xml`/`robots.txt` (DR-022); `verify` fails on drift.
6. GitHub Pages + offline + responsive + accessible + print-friendly.
7. Evidence over assumption; mark opinion vs fact.
8. One topic, one authoritative home — no duplication.
9. Reusable render functions, not copy-pasted markup.
10. Publication quality — no placeholders as finished.

## Process

- One milestone at a time; next only after explicit owner accept.
- Architecture: Analyze → Plan → Sync docs → Debt review → Implement → Self-review → PR summary → Commit msg.
- Commit only when the user explicitly asks.
- Milestone done → test plan in `17_TESTING_GUIDE.md` + share with owner (`15_RELEASE_PROCESS.md`).
- Unexpected repo state → stop and report; don’t silently overwrite.

## Escalation

If uncertain, or irreversible/architecturally significant — ask first.
